<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Weather App</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="/img/weather.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
    <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/b1a8a7536f.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <style>
        #menu-toggle:checked+#menu {
            display: block;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body class='flex flex-col min-h-screen bg-teal-200 text-indigo-900'>
    {{>header}}
    <main class='bg-gray-100 flex-grow flex'>
        <div class="mx-4 sm:mx-8 lg:mx-16 my-2 sm:my-6 lg:my-8 ">
            <h1 class="text-center uppercase text-xl sm:text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-semibold">{{title}}</h1>
            <img class="h-40 sm:h-48 md:h-56 lg:h-64 w-full object-contain mt-4 mb-6 sm:mb-8 md:mb-12 lg:mb-16"
                src="/img/canIHelpYou.jpeg" alt="picture of maria del carmen from santiagocodes" />
            <div class="leading-7 lg:text-xl leading-relaxed lg:leading-loose">
                <p class='font-semibold'>What is this webpage?</p>
                <p>This is a very simple webpage that tells users about the weather at any location in the world.</p>
                <br>
                <p class='font-semibold'>How does it work?</p>
                <p>It is very simple. Click on the 'weather' tab. On this page the user will find an input box where
                    he/she can type in the location they want. Click the 'search' button beside the input box and voil√†!
                </p>
                <br>
                <p class='font-semibold'>I followed the instructions, but got the weather information from some other
                    place. What can I do?</p>
                <p>I would suggest the users to be more specific with their queries. What does this mean? Do not just
                    type in the city name. Try to type in the country's name as well.</p>
                <br>
                <p class='font-semibold'>Are you a fellow developer?</p>
                <p>If you are a developer and want to take a look at the code you can do so <a
                        href="https://github.com/santiagocodes/node-udemy-course">here</a>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
    {{>footer}}
</body>

</html>